'''Bartlett Glacier''' ({{Coord|86|15|S|152|0|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a tributary [[glacier]], about {{convert|30|nmi|km|-1}} long and {{convert|5|nmi|km|-1}} wide at its terminus, flowing northeast from [[Nilsen Plateau]] and joining [[Scott Glacier (Transantarctic Mountains)|Scott Glacier]] close north of [[Mount Gardiner]]. It was discovered in December 1934 by the [[Byrd Antarctic Expedition]] geological party under [[Quin Blackburn]], and named by [[Richard E. Byrd]] for Captain [[Robert A. Bartlett]] of [[Brigus]], Newfoundland, a noted Arctic navigator and explorer who recommended that the expedition acquire the [[USS Bear (1874)|''Bear'']], an ice-ship which was purchased and rechristened by Byrd as the ''Bear of Oakland''.<ref name=gnis/>

