A '''Chequered retreat''', (''retraite en échiquier'', Fr.) is so called from the several component parts of a pre-mechanised line or [[battalion]], which alternately retreat and face about in the presence of an enemy, exhibiting the figure of the chequered squares upon a [[chess board]].{{sfn|James|1816|p=845}}

