{{speciesbox | name = Chiapan climbing rat | status = CR | status_system = IUCN3.1 | genus = Tylomys | species = bullaris | authority = [[Clinton Hart Merriam|Merriam]], 1901 | synonyms = }}
The '''Chiapan climbing rat''' ('''''Tylomys bullaris''''') is a species of [[rodent]] in the family [[Cricetidae]]. It is found only in [[Mexico]]. The species is known from only one location in [[Tuxtla Gutierrez]], [[Chiapas]]. The habitat in the region is being converted to agricultural and urban use, which is likely causing critical declines in numbers of ''T. bullaris''.<ref name=iucn>{{Cite journal | author = Álvarez-Castañeda, S.T. | author2 = Castro-Arellano, I. | last-author-amp = yes | title = ''Tylomys bullaris'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 2008 | page = e.T22570A9376729 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 2008 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/22570/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2008.RLTS.T22570A9376729.en | access-date = 10 January 2018}}</ref>
