[[Image:Olof Fåhræus (1796–1884, ur Svenska Familj-Journalen).png|thumb|Olof Fåhræus (1796-1884)]]
'''Olof Immanuel Fåhræus''' (23 March 1796 in [[Slite]] &ndash; 28 May 1884 in [[Gotland]] or [[Stockholm]]), was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] politician and [[entomologist]] mainly interested in [[Coleoptera]]. 

His collection is shared between  the natural history museums of Stockholm and [[Gothenburg]]. He wrote, with [[Carl Henrik Boheman]] ''Insecta Caffrariae annis 1838-1845 a [[Johan August Wahlberg|J.A. Wahlberg]] collecta. Coleoptera''. Holmiae : Fritze & Norstedt Vol. 1 pp.&nbsp;299–625 published in 1851. 

He was elected a member of the [[Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences]] in 1840.

