'''Stodtmeister cells''' are a sub-classification of [[neutrophil]]s exhibiting a [[Pelger-Huet anomaly]] with a non-lobed [[Cell nucleus|nucleus]] that may appear round or oval shaped.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Lynch|first1=Edward C|title=Clinical Methods: The History, Physical, and Laboratory Examinations. 3rd edition.|date=1990|publisher=Butterworths|location=Boston}}</ref>

